        "@value": "https://nac-cna.ca/en/event/38433"
      }
    ],
    "http://ogp.me/ns#title": [
      {
        "@language": "en-ca",
        "@value": "Shelley, Ehnes, Altstaedt | Clara, Robert, Johannes: Coda |  Thu, Jul 2, 2026, 8:00 pm | Southam Hall"
      }
    ],
    "http://ogp.me/ns#image": [
      {
        "@language": "en-ca",
        "@value": "https://naccnaca-eventimages.s3.amazonaws.com/38433/20__large.jpg"
      }
    ],
    "http://ogp.me/ns#description": [
      {
        "@language": "en-ca",
        "@value": "Three things to know:\n\n\n\tExplore the personal and artistic ties that bound three giants of German Romanticism: Johannes Brahms and Clara and Robert Schumann.\n\tA pair of concertos in this program represents the final works Johannes Brahms and Robert Schumann ever wrote for orchestra.\n\tClara Schumann wasn’t just a talented composer—she was one of Europe’s most in-demand piano soloists for 63 years.\n\n\nThe relationship between Johannes Brahms and the Schumanns—composer-pianists Clara and Robert—is one of the most moving in music history. As friends, romantic..."
      }
    ],
    "http://ogp.me/ns/fb#admins": [
      {
        "@language": "en-ca",
        "@value": "728780803"
      }
